<H1><A NAME="SECTION00020000000000000000">
Centralizer Coalgebras</A>
</H1>

<P>
Let <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img3.png"
 ALT="$R$"> be a noetherian integral domain, <IMG
 WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img5.png"
 ALT="$V$"> a free
<IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img3.png"
 ALT="$R$">-module with a fixed basis <!-- MATH
 $\{v_{1}, \ldots , v_{n}\}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img6.png"
 ALT="$\{v_{1}, \ldots , v_{n}\}$">. Let
<IMG
 WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img7.png"
 ALT="$e_{i}^{ j}$"> denote the corresponding basis of matrix units for
<!-- MATH
 ${\cal E}:={\rm End}_{R}{(V)}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="121" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img8.png"
 ALT="${\cal E}:={\rm End}_{R}{(V)}$">. The algebra structure on <IMG
 WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img9.png"
 ALT="${\cal E}$"> induces a
coalgebra structure on the dual <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img3.png"
 ALT="$R$">-module
<!-- MATH
 ${{\cal E}}^*:={\rm Hom}_{R}{({\cal E},R)}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="153" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img10.png"
 ALT="${{\cal E}}^*:={\rm Hom}_{R}{({\cal E},R)}$">. On the dual basis elements the comultiplication
<IMG
 WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img11.png"
 ALT="$\Delta $"> and the counit <IMG
 WIDTH="12" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img12.png"
 ALT="$\epsilon $"> are given by

<P>
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH
 \begin{displaymath}
\Delta ({{e}^*_{i}}^{j})=\sum_{k=1}^n {{e}^*_{i}}^{k}  \otimes {{e}^*_{k}}^{j} ,\; \; \epsilon ({{e}^*_{i}}^{j})
=\delta_{ij}.
\end{displaymath}
 -->

<IMG
 WIDTH="426" HEIGHT="62" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img13.png"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}\Delta ({{e}^*_{i}}^{j})=\sum_{k=1}^n {{e}^*_{i}}^{k} \otimes {{e}^*_{k}}^{j} ,\; \; \epsilon ({{e}^*_{i}}^{j})
=\delta_{ij}.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>

<P>
We will be engaged with epimorphic coalgebra images of <IMG
 WIDTH="24" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img14.png"
 ALT="${{\cal E}}^*$"> since
they correspond to subalgebras of <IMG
 WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img9.png"
 ALT="${\cal E}$">. Consider the isomorphism
<!-- MATH
 ${\vartheta}_{tr}:{\cal E}\rightarrow {{\cal E}}^*$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="104" HEIGHT="35" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img15.png"
 ALT="${\vartheta}_{tr}:{\cal E}\rightarrow {{\cal E}}^*$"> of <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img3.png"
 ALT="$R$">-modules induced by 
the nondegenerate bilinear form corresponding to 
the matrix trace map <!-- MATH
 $tr:{\cal E}\rightarrow R$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="92" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img16.png"
 ALT="$tr:{\cal E}\rightarrow R$">, i.e. <!-- MATH
 ${\vartheta}_{tr}(\mu)(\nu):= tr(\mu\nu)$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="161" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img17.png"
 ALT="${\vartheta}_{tr}(\mu)(\nu):= tr(\mu\nu)$">.
Note that <!-- MATH
 ${\vartheta}_{tr}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="28" HEIGHT="35" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img18.png"
 ALT="${\vartheta}_{tr}$"> maps <IMG
 WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img7.png"
 ALT="$e_{i}^{ j}$"> onto <!-- MATH
 ${{e}^*_{j}}^{i}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="26" HEIGHT="41" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img19.png"
 ALT="${{e}^*_{j}}^{i}$">.
Let <!-- MATH
 $A\subseteq {\cal E}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="56" HEIGHT="35" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img20.png"
 ALT="$A\subseteq {\cal E}$"> be an arbitrary
subset and <IMG
 WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img21.png"
 ALT="$L(A)$"> the <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img3.png"
 ALT="$R$">-linear span in <IMG
 WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img9.png"
 ALT="${\cal E}$"> of all commutators
<!-- MATH
 $[\nu, \mu ]=\nu\mu-\mu\nu$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="136" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img22.png"
 ALT="$[\nu, \mu ]=\nu\mu-\mu\nu$"> where <IMG
 WIDTH="15" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img23.png"
 ALT="$\nu$"> runs through <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img24.png"
 ALT="$A$"> and <IMG
 WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="33" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img25.png"
 ALT="$\mu$">
runs through <IMG
 WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img9.png"
 ALT="${\cal E}$">. We set <!-- MATH
 $K(A):={\vartheta}_{tr}(L(A))\subseteq {{\cal E}}^*$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="205" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img26.png"
 ALT="$K(A):={\vartheta}_{tr}(L(A))\subseteq {{\cal E}}^*$">. If <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img24.png"
 ALT="$A$"> consists of
just one element <IMG
 WIDTH="15" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img23.png"
 ALT="$\nu$"> we use abbreviations <IMG
 WIDTH="42" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img27.png"
 ALT="$L(\nu)$"> and <IMG
 WIDTH="47" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img28.png"
 ALT="$K(\nu)$">
for <IMG
 WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img21.png"
 ALT="$L(A)$"> and <IMG
 WIDTH="50" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img29.png"
 ALT="$K(A)$">.

<P>
<P>
<DIV><A NAME="Koideal"><B>Lemma  2.1</B></A> &nbsp; 
<IMG
 WIDTH="50" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img29.png"
 ALT="$K(A)$"> is a coideal in <IMG
 WIDTH="24" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img14.png"
 ALT="${{\cal E}}^*$"> for each subset <!-- MATH
 $A\subseteq {\cal E}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="56" HEIGHT="35" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img20.png"
 ALT="$A\subseteq {\cal E}$">.</DIV><P></P>

<P>
S<SMALL>KETCH OF </SMALL>P<SMALL>ROOF: </SMALL>Since the sum of coideals is a coideal again we only need to consider
the case <IMG
 WIDTH="73" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img30.png"
 ALT="$A=\{\nu\}$">. Using an explicit expression for <IMG
 WIDTH="15" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img23.png"
 ALT="$\nu$"> 
in terms of the basiselements <IMG
 WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img7.png"
 ALT="$e_{i}^{ j}$"> one
calculates for arbitrary numbers <!-- MATH
 $k,l \in \{1,\ldots, n\}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="134" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img31.png"
 ALT="$k,l \in \{1,\ldots, n\}$">:

<P>
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH
 \begin{displaymath}
\Delta ({\vartheta}_{tr}([\nu ,e_{k}^{ l}]))=
\sum_m (
{{e}^*_{l}}^{m}\otimes{\vartheta}_{tr}([\nu,e_{k}^{ m}]) +
{\vartheta}_{tr}([\nu, {{e}^*_{m}}^{l}]) \otimes {{e}^*_{m}}^{k},
\end{displaymath}
 -->

<IMG
 WIDTH="522" HEIGHT="52" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img32.png"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}\Delta ({\vartheta}_{tr}([\nu ,e_{k}^{ l}]))=
\sum_m (
{{e}^*...
...artheta}_{tr}([\nu, {{e}^*_{m}}^{l}]) \otimes {{e}^*_{m}}^{k},
\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>

<P>
which just means

<P>
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH
 \begin{displaymath}
\Delta (K(\nu)) \subseteq K(\nu) \otimes {{\cal E}}^*+ {{\cal E}}^*
\otimes K(\nu).
\end{displaymath}
 -->

<IMG
 WIDTH="427" HEIGHT="33" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img33.png"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}\Delta (K(\nu)) \subseteq K(\nu) \otimes {{\cal E}}^*+ {{\cal E}}^*
\otimes K(\nu). \end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>

<P>
In a simialar way one shows <!-- MATH
 $\epsilon (K(\nu))=0$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="103" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img34.png"
 ALT="$\epsilon (K(\nu))=0$">. A more detailed proof
can be found in section 1.3 of
[<A
 HREF="node9.html#doc">Oe</A>].<IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img35.png"
 ALT="$\Box$">
<BR><P>
If <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img36.png"
 ALT="$C$"> is an arbitrary coalgebra such that <IMG
 WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img5.png"
 ALT="$V$"> is a <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img36.png"
 ALT="$C$">-comodule
with structure map <!-- MATH
 $\tau_{V}:V\rightarrow V\otimes C$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="138" HEIGHT="35" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img37.png"
 ALT="$\tau_{V}:V\rightarrow V\otimes C$"> we denote the set of <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img36.png"
 ALT="$C$">-comodule
endomorphisms by

<P>
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH
 \begin{displaymath}
{\rm End}_{C}{(V)}:=\{
\mu \in {\cal E}|\; \; (\mu \otimes {\rm id}_{C}) \circ \tau_{V}= \tau_{V} 
\circ \mu \}.
\end{displaymath}
 -->

<IMG
 WIDTH="468" HEIGHT="33" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img38.png"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}{\rm End}_{C}{(V)}:=\{
\mu \in {\cal E}\vert\; \; (\mu \otimes {\rm id}_{C}) \circ \tau_{V}= \tau_{V}
\circ \mu \}.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>

<P>
Clearly this is a subalgebra of <IMG
 WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img9.png"
 ALT="${\cal E}$">. The proof of the next lemma is
similar to the preceeding one.

<P>
<P>
<DIV><A NAME="Koalgebren_Endomorphismen"><B>Lemma  2.2</B></A> &nbsp; 
Let <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img36.png"
 ALT="$C$"> be a coalgebra together with an epimorphism
<!-- MATH
 $\pi: {{\cal E}}^*\rightarrow C$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="96" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img39.png"
 ALT="$\pi: {{\cal E}}^*\rightarrow C$">. Then
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH
 \begin{displaymath}
\mu \in {\rm End}_{C}{(V)} \Longleftrightarrow K(\mu)  \subseteq {\rm ker}(\pi).
\end{displaymath}
 -->

<IMG
 WIDTH="418" HEIGHT="33" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img40.png"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}\mu \in {\rm End}_{C}{(V)} \Longleftrightarrow K(\mu) \subseteq {\rm ker}(\pi).
\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P></DIV><P></P>

<P>
<P>
<DIV><A NAME="Verknupfungstreue"><B>Corollary  2.3</B></A> &nbsp; 
Let <IMG
 WIDTH="25" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img41.png"
 ALT="$M$"> be a coideal in <IMG
 WIDTH="24" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img14.png"
 ALT="${{\cal E}}^*$"> and <!-- MATH
 $\mu , \nu \in {\cal E}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="70" HEIGHT="35" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img42.png"
 ALT="$\mu , \nu \in {\cal E}$">. Then
<!-- MATH
 $K(\mu)  \subseteq M$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img43.png"
 ALT="$K(\mu) \subseteq M$"> and <!-- MATH
 $K(\nu) \subseteq M$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="92" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
