 $K(\mu \nu) \subseteq M$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="104" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img45.png"
 ALT="$K(\mu \nu) \subseteq M$"> and <!-- MATH
 $K(\nu\mu ) \subseteq M$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="104" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img46.png"
 ALT="$K(\nu\mu ) \subseteq M$">.</DIV><P></P>

<P>
We now define the <EM>centralizer coalgebra</EM> of the subset
<!-- MATH
 $A\subseteq{\cal E}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="56" HEIGHT="35" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img20.png"
 ALT="$A\subseteq {\cal E}$"> as
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH
 \begin{displaymath}
M(A):={{\cal E}}^*/ K(A).
\end{displaymath}
 -->

<IMG
 WIDTH="358" HEIGHT="33" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img47.png"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}M(A):={{\cal E}}^*/ K(A).\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>
According to
lemma
<A HREF="node2.html#Koalgebren_Endomorphismen">2.2</A> we have
<BR><P></P>
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
<!-- MATH
 \begin{displaymath}
A \subseteq {\rm End}_{M(A)}{(V)}.
\end{displaymath}
 -->

<IMG
 WIDTH="350" HEIGHT="34" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img48.png"
 ALT="\begin{displaymath}A \subseteq {\rm End}_{M(A)}{(V)}.\end{displaymath}">
</DIV>
<BR CLEAR="ALL">
<P></P>
Furthermore <IMG
 WIDTH="53" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img49.png"
 ALT="$M(A)$"> is the largest epimorphic image of <IMG
 WIDTH="24" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img14.png"
 ALT="${{\cal E}}^*$"> with this
property. By the corollary <IMG
 WIDTH="53" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img49.png"
 ALT="$M(A)$"> does not change if <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img24.png"
 ALT="$A$"> is substituted
